The paper deals with the problem of measuring the disclosure of a secret in a probabilistic transition system, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The use of Interval-valued Discrete Time Markov Chains (IDTMCs) and refinement techniques suggests a connection to formal methods and logic (cs.LO). The paper also mentions scheduling and concrete implementations, which are topics related to programming languages (cs.PL) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of ω-regular predicates and probability computations suggests a connection to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI).
